description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for motivated Doctors with an interest in Emergency Medicine to develop their knowledge and skills in an innovative and busy trauma centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Fellow posts which would be suitable for a doctor who has completed Foundation Training or the equivalent [ideally including an EM post].&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Substantive/ fixed term I year [extendable by mutual consent] full time posts. [shorter posts also considered]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plus opportunities for part-time/job shares.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will work on the Clinical Fellow rota on a full shift pattern including nights. Applicant’s with more extensive EM experience may be able to work on the senior middle grade rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will include paid regular teaching and involvement in journal club [looking at critical appraisal of journals] and with the opportunity to get involved in audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All posts include a paid CPD day each week, encouraged and supported to develop personal educational interests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is well supported with senior middle grades and consultants who work a 24/7 rota. UHCW is a major trauma centre and the clinical fellows are an integral part of the trauma team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Fellows are all allocated an Education Supervisor on starting a post and undergo regular appraisal and support of their educational needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that UHCW NHS Trust does not sponsor applications for GMC registration and therefore successful candidates will be required to obtain this through alternative routes if they are not already registered with a licence to practice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For information about the different routes to apply please contact the General Medical Council directly or visit their website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameNicki WilliamsJob titleED consultantEmail addressnichola.williams@uhcw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
